         <abstract>
            <p>An integer $a$ is called a congruent number if and only if there are positive integer solutions to the system of equations $$x^2 + ay^2 = z^2\quad \text{and}\quad x^2 - ay^2 = t^2.$$ In this note congruent numbers are discussed and a table of known square-free congruent numbers less than 1000 is exhibited.</p>
          </abstract>
